Class NumStack

  • java.lang.Object
    • calc.model.NumStack

  • public class NumStack
extends java.lang.Object
    The NumStack class defines the stack of numeric values, read from a reverse polish expression.

    1.0
    Author:
    Alex Cordaro ZDAC051

      • pop

        public float pop()
          throws BadTypeException,
                 EmptyStackException
        Pops the top entry from the stack, by calling the pop() method of the Stack object, then returning it's numeric value.
        Returns:
        numeric value of the top entry
        Throws:
        BadTypeException - when the top entry is not of numeric type
        EmptyStackException - when the stack is empty, thus no entry can be popped
